# backend/ — Node.js/Fastify Real-Time Backend

## Purpose
Handles all real-time and payment-sensitive features: auctions (bidding), chat, push notifications,
payment processing (Midtrans), admin operations, and file uploads.
Also exposes /internal/* routes for PHP → Node calls.

## Framework & Key Libraries
- Fastify 4.26 + TypeScript
- Socket.io (WebSocket for auctions + chat)
- pg (PostgreSQL connection pool)
- ioredis (Redis client)
- Bull (job queues for notification delivery)
- jsonwebtoken + bcryptjs (auth)
- web-push (VAPID push notifications)
- @midtrans/snap (payment gateway)

## Entry Point
backend/index.ts — registers all plugins, routes, socket handlers, queues, starts HTTP server.

## Directory Map
```
backend/src/
├── config/
│   ├── database.ts    pg Pool (DB_HOST, DB_USER, DB_PASS, DB_NAME)
│   └── redis.ts       ioredis client (REDIS_HOST, REDIS_PORT)
├── controllers/       Request handlers (7 files)
│   ├── adminController.ts
│   ├── auctionController.ts
│   ├── auctionNotificationController.ts
│   ├── orderNotificationController.ts
│   ├── paymentController.ts
│   ├── notificationController.ts
│   └── reviewController.ts
├── middleware/
│   └── authMiddleware.ts  JWT verification (Authorization: Bearer <token>)
├── routes/
│   ├── adminRoutes.ts       /admin/*
│   ├── auctionRoutes.ts     /auctions/*
│   ├── authRoutes.ts        /auth/*
│   ├── chatRoutes.ts        /chat/*
│   ├── notificationRoutes.ts /notifications/*
│   ├── paymentRoutes.ts     /payment/*
│   ├── internalRoutes.ts    /internal/* (PHP → Node, requires INTERNAL_API_KEY header)
│   └── uploadRoutes.ts      POST / (file upload → ./storage/)
├── services/
│   ├── paymentService.ts      Midtrans snap token generation
│   ├── notificationService.ts Web Push delivery via VAPID
│   └── auctionService.ts      Auction business logic
├── sockets/
│   ├── auctionSocket.ts   Socket.io auction room — bid placement, auction end events
│   └── chatSocket.ts      Socket.io chat — room join, message send/receive
├── queues/
│   └── notificationQueue.ts  Bull queue — async push notification processing
├── repositories/      Data access layer — pg queries
└── scripts/
    └── seedAdmin.ts   Creates initial admin user (npm run seed:admin)
```

## Environment Variables Required
- DB_HOST, DB_USER, DB_PASS, DB_NAME (PostgreSQL)
- REDIS_HOST, REDIS_PORT
- JWT_SECRET
- PORT (= NODE_PORT, default 3000)
- VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY, VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY, VAPID_SUBJECT
- INTERNAL_API_KEY (shared secret with PHP)
- CLIENT_URL (CORS origin)
- MIDTRANS_SERVER_KEY, MIDTRANS_CLIENT_KEY, MIDTRANS_IS_PRODUCTION

## Dev (outside Docker)
- npm run dev:watch → nodemon --exec ts-node index.ts (restart on save)
- For true fast reload: replace with tsx watch index.ts

## Build & Run
- Dev: npm run dev:watch
- Build: npm run build (tsc → dist/)
- Start: npm run start
- Seed admin: npm run seed:admin
